sub: 'Search App Store apps, compare prices across regions, and auto-convert to CNY.',
intro: {
heading: 'About This Tool',
p1: 'App Store prices can vary significantly between countries and regions. The same app might cost $4.99 in the US but the equivalent of $3.20 in another country after currency conversion. Tax policies, exchange rate fluctuations, and Apple\u2019s tiered pricing system all contribute to these regional price differences.',
p2: 'Our Price Compare tool queries the Apple iTunes Search API across 9 major App Store regions — including China, United States, Japan, Hong Kong, United Kingdom, Korea, and others — and auto-converts all prices to Chinese Yuan (CNY) using live exchange rates. The lowest price is highlighted with a badge so you can spot the best deal at a glance.',
p3: 'To use it, type an app name (like "Procreate" or "GoodNotes"), an App Store Track ID (the number after "id" in the URL), or paste a full App Store link. The tool supports both lookup by ID and search by keyword. Results show the app icon, developer name, bundle ID, and a comparison table with prices for every supported region.',
p4: 'Tips: Use exact names for better matches. For apps with region-specific listings, try searching in the base country where the app is primarily distributed. Exchange rates update on each search — if you see unusual conversions, simply search again to refresh.',
},
