heading: 'Common Issues',
items: [
'App is no longer free: free promotions typically last 24-72 hours. Check the timestamp on the listing — if it is older than 3 days, the app may have returned to paid status.',
'App shows as free but App Store lists a price: the promotion window may have ended between our last refresh and your check. Always verify on the App Store before relying on displayed data.',
'IAP-heavy apps appear in results: the tool detects price changes to free, not app monetization model. Some developers make the app free but monetize through aggressive IAP — check the IAP section before downloading.',
'Duplicate entries: some apps appear in multiple categories. This is expected behavior — the app genuinely fits multiple category definitions in the App Store.',
],
