icon: {
title: 'Icon Lookup',
sub: 'Search App Store apps and copy high-resolution icon links.',
intro: {
heading: 'About Icon Lookup',
p1: 'Every app on the App Store has a high-resolution icon — typically 1024x1024 pixels — stored on Apple\'s CDN. These icons are perfect for app reviews, design inspiration, mockups, blog posts, or simply appreciating the artwork behind your favorite apps. Our Icon Lookup tool makes it trivially easy to find and copy these icons.',
p2: 'Search by app name or browse by region. The tool queries the iTunes Search API, fetches app metadata including the icon URL, and automatically rewrites it to the 1024x1024 version (the highest resolution Apple serves). Results show the app icon at full resolution, app name, developer, genre, and price.',
p3: 'Each result card includes three actions: "App Store" opens the official listing, "Copy Icon" copies the direct icon URL to your clipboard, and "Full Size" opens the icon at full resolution in a new tab where you can save it. The search supports all major App Store regions for region-specific app discovery.',
p4: 'Tip: some apps use region-specific icons — try switching between US and China App Stores to see if the icon differs. For app bundles or Apple Arcade games, the icon URL may redirect — right-click "Full Size" to save directly. The copied URLs are direct CDN links usable in any browser or design tool.',
},
tips: {
heading: 'Pro Tips',
items: [
'1024x1024 resolution: the tool automatically rewrites icon URLs to fetch the highest available resolution from Apple CDN.',
'Design inspiration: browse icons by genre to study design trends — great for UI/UX designers and app developers.',
'Icon history: some apps change icons with major updates. Search periodically to track visual rebranding over time.',
'Batch workflow: search, copy icon URL, paste into your design tool — the whole flow takes seconds.',
'App discovery: browsing icons often surfaces interesting apps you would not have found through text search alone.',
],
},
placeholder: 'Enter app name, e.g. Procreate / WeChat / Notion',
howItWorks: {
heading: 'How It Works',
p1: 'The Icon Lookup tool queries the iTunes Search API to find apps matching your search term, then extracts the icon URL from each app\u2019s artwork metadata. Apple stores app icons on a CDN at multiple resolutions (60x60, 100x100, 512x512, 1024x1024). The tool rewrites the URL to always fetch the 1024x1024 version — the highest resolution Apple serves publicly.',
p2: 'Search queries can target any App Store region. The tool passes the country code parameter to the iTunes Search API, returning results as they appear in that region\u2019s store. This is useful for checking region-specific icons — some apps use different artwork for different markets. The search also supports Chinese, Japanese, Korean, and other non-Latin app names.',
p3: 'Each result card provides three quick actions: open the App Store listing, copy the direct icon URL to clipboard, or view the icon at full resolution in a new tab. The direct CDN URLs are permanent (they do not expire) and can be embedded in websites, design mockups, blog posts, or presentation slides without hosting the image yourself.',
},
troubleshooting: {
heading: 'Common Issues',
items: [
'Icon not loading: some apps use region-specific CDN paths. Try switching to a different App Store region in the search dropdown to see if the icon loads from that region\u2019s CDN.',
'Low resolution despite 1024x1024 URL: some very old or obscure apps never uploaded a 1024x1024 icon. In these cases, Apple defaults to the highest available resolution (usually 512x512).',
'Icon differs from what you see on device: apps can update their icons with version updates. The tool shows the current App Store icon, which should match the latest version. If not, the CDN may be caching an older version temporarily.',
'Apple Arcade and bundle icons: apps distributed exclusively through Apple Arcade or as part of bundles may have different icon URLs. These are still accessible but may redirect through Apple\u2019s offer pages.',
],
},
