proxy: {
title: 'Proxy Scripts',
sub: 'Shadowrocket, Surge, Loon, Quantumult X, Stash config entries.',
intro: {
heading: 'About Proxy Config Navigator',
p1: 'Proxy clients on iOS — including Shadowrocket, Surge, Loon, Quantumult X, and Stash — use configuration files to define routing rules, ad-blocking scripts, and network rewrite behaviors. The iOS proxy community maintains numerous open-source config repositories on GitHub, each optimized for different use cases: ad blocking, privacy enhancement, regional access, or lightweight performance.',
p2: 'Our Proxy Config Navigator indexes these community configs into a searchable, filterable directory. Each entry includes the config type (ad-blocking rules, rewrite scripts, or routing rules), category (full config vs. specialized), client compatibility, GitHub repository source, star count, last update date, and config file size. This saves you from digging through GitHub repos manually.',
p3: 'Use the filter controls to narrow by type (adblock, routing, rewrite, lite versions) and the sort options to rank by popularity (stars), recency (last updated), name, or file size. The search box supports keyword matching across config names, authors, and clients. Recommended configs — community-vetted, well-maintained options — are highlighted with a badge.',
p4: 'Tip: "Lite" configs are ideal for older devices or light usage — they use less memory and CPU. For comprehensive coverage, look for full configs with high star counts and recent updates. Always review config rules before deployment — some configs may have region-specific settings that need adjustment for your network environment.',
},
tips: {
heading: 'Pro Tips',
items: [
'Star count signals quality: higher GitHub stars usually mean community-tested and actively maintained configurations.',
'Update recency matters: configs updated within the last month are more likely to work with current app versions and network conditions.',
'Size vs features: larger config files cover more apps but consume more device resources. Choose based on your device capabilities.',
'Recommended badge: these configs have been reviewed for quality, safety, and reliability — start here if unsure.',
'Mix and match: advanced users often combine a routing config with a separate adblock config for customized coverage.',
],
},
placeholder: 'Search config name / author / client',
howItWorks: {
heading: 'How It Works',
p1: 'The Proxy Config Navigator aggregates configuration files from community-maintained GitHub repositories into a searchable directory. Each config entry is a text-based rules file that proxy clients (Shadowrocket, Surge, Loon, Quantumult X, Stash) load to define how network traffic is routed, which domains to block, and which URLs to rewrite.',
p2: 'Configs are categorized by function: Adblock configs contain domain blocklists and pattern-matching rules to filter ads at the DNS or HTTP level. Routing configs define which traffic goes through a proxy and which uses direct connection — essential for split-tunneling setups. Rewrite configs modify HTTP requests and responses, commonly used for removing in-app ads, unlocking region-restricted content, or modifying API behavior.',
p3: 'The directory updates periodically by re-indexing the source GitHub repositories. Each entry displays the config type, supported clients, star count (community approval signal), last commit date (freshness indicator), and file size (complexity indicator). The recommended badge highlights configs that have been community-vetted for quality, safety, and maintenance reliability.',
},
troubleshooting: {
heading: 'Common Issues',
items: [
'Config not working after import: ensure your proxy client is updated to the latest version. Some configs use features only available in newer client releases.',
'Conflicts with existing rules: importing multiple configs can cause rule priority conflicts. Most clients allow you to adjust rule ordering to resolve this.',
'Recommended config still shows ads: no adblock config catches 100% of ads. Regional ad networks and dynamically served ads may bypass rule-based blocking. Combine multiple config types for better coverage.',
'Config file too large for device: lite versions are available for most popular configs — these strip non-essential rules to reduce memory usage and processing overhead on older devices.',
],
},
